The creator of award-wining drama series Lockdown, Mandla Ngcongwane vowed to maintain the element of surprise in its upcoming season 5. The popular Mzansi Magic explosive drama tells the tale of prison inmates while also expanding its narratives to include different motifs such as love and sacrifice. Starring the likes of Zola Nombona, the 30-minute-long episodes will introduce new characters, said Ngcongwane. “This season will be introducing characters like Sophie Ndaba and Patrick Moloi, this will make the storytelling aspect bigger,” he said. Although holding the cards close to his chest Mandla said the new season will start at the end of the month. He added that the production team did not compromise on the unique aspects of what made the show so popular. 